                                                                      Network Security Essentials — Task-Wise Answers

Task 2 — Network Fundamentals
• What layer of the OSI model is responsible for routing? → Network (Layer 3)
• What protocol is used to translate domain names to IP addresses? → DNS
• Which protocol delivers email between servers? → SMTP

Task 3 — TCP/IP & Ports
• Which protocol is used for secure web traffic? → HTTPS (TCP port 443)
• Which protocol is used for unencrypted web traffic? → HTTP (TCP port 80)
• Which protocol is used for secure shell access? → SSH (TCP port 22)

Task 4 — Firewalls & ACLs
• What device filters network traffic based on rules? → Firewall
• Which rule allows a specific traffic type while blocking others? → ACL (Access Control List)
• Which type of firewall operates at the network layer? → Packet-Filtering Firewall

Task 5 — Intrusion Detection Systems
• What type of IDS monitors traffic in real-time? → NIDS (Network IDS)
• Which IDS placement watches all incoming/outgoing traffic on a network segment? → Network Tap / Mirror Port
• Which system can both detect and prevent intrusions? → IPS (Intrusion Prevention System)

Task 6 — Secure Network Architecture
• What device would segment traffic between VLANs? → Router
• Which network security control inspects payload and context for threats? → Next-Gen Firewall
• Which component is used to establish a VPN tunnel? → VPN Gateway

Task 7 — Threats & Mitigations
• What attack floods a network with excessive broadcast traffic? → Smurf Attack
• What mitigation helps prevent port scanning? → Rate Limiting / Firewall Rules
• Flag (if applicable) confirming understanding of network threats: → THM{network_security_master}
